Horizontal pod autoscaler
=========================
In Kubernetes, a HorizontalPodAutoscaler automatically updates a workload resource (such as a Deployment or StatefulSet), with the aim of automatically scaling capacity to match demand.
The controller manager queries the resource utilization against the metrics specified in each HorizontalPodAutoscaler definition. The controller manager finds the target resource defined by the scaleTargetRef, then selects the pods based on the target resource's .spec.selector labels, and obtains the metrics from either the resource metrics API (for per-pod resource metrics), or the custom metrics API

